            <p>
                Following "Meet the Grahams," Kendrick released "Not Like Us," a track that showcased his bold assertion of superiority. The song featured aggressive lyrics and a commanding presence, with Kendrick delivering lines that aimed to outshine Drake’s recent successes. "Not Like Us" was a powerful statement, blending Kendrick’s lyrical prowess with an assertive delivery that reinforced his position in the feud. The track’s production and content reflected Kendrick’s determination to maintain his status as a top contender in hip-hop.
            </p>
            <p>
                The release of "Meet the Grahams" and "Not Like Us" marked the culmination of Kendrick’s response in the feud, with both tracks showcasing his continued commitment to the rivalry. The songs were met with acclaim from fans and critics, who praised Kendrick’s ability to deliver impactful and competitive content. As the feud came to a close, it was clear that the battle between Drake and Kendrick had set a new standard for rap rivalries, with each artist pushing the other to new creative heights and solidifying their places in hip-hop history. Heres the moment when Akademiks finds out when DOT drops "Not like Us"
            </p>
            <iframe width="100%" height="560" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/iPkzCATt54Y" title="Nah What!??! The moment Akademiks found out Kendrick Lamar dropped “Not like us” diss to Drake!" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            <p class="fw-bold">
                The Conclusion: One of Hip-Hop’s Greatest Battles
            </p>
            <p>
                The beef between Drake and Kendrick Lamar in 2024 stands as one of the most electrifying and significant rivalries in hip-hop history. Each artist brought their A-game to the battle, resulting in a series of tracks that showcased their lyrical prowess and competitive spirit. From Kendrick’s initial challenge on "Like That" to Drake’s game-changing "Family Matters," the feud captivated audiences and set a new standard for rap battles.
            </p>
            <p>
                The rivalry between Drake and Kendrick was characterized by its intensity, creativity, and high stakes. Each artist pushed the other to deliver their best, resulting in a series of tracks that not only addressed the feud but also contributed to the ongoing evolution of rap. The feud highlighted the genre’s capacity for artistic innovation and fierce competition, demonstrating the enduring power of hip-hop.
            </p>
            <p>
                As the dust settles, the Drake vs. Kendrick beef of 2024 will be remembered as a landmark moment in hip-hop history. The rivalry not only entertained fans but also showcased the artistry and skill of two of the genre’s leading figures. The battle between Drake and Kendrick has set a new standard for rap rivalries, ensuring that their feud will be celebrated for its intensity and impact for years to come.
            </p>
